dwm - dynamic window manager (flexipatch build)
================================================
This is a custom dwm build based on bakkeby/dwm-flexipatch 6.8,
configured for daily use on Xubuntu with the following patches enabled:

  vanitygaps, cfacts, focusstack (stacker), bottomstack, movestack,
  systray, alwayscenter, shiftview, autostart, seamless restart
  (preserveonrestart), restartsig, selfrestart, dragmfact


Requirements
------------
In order to build dwm you need the Xlib header files and the following
build dependencies:

    sudo apt install -y \
        build-essential \
        libx11-dev \
        libxft-dev \
        libxinerama-dev \
        libxext-dev \
        git \
        xterm


Runtime Dependencies
--------------------
These packages are required for the full setup to work correctly.
Install them all at once with:

    sudo apt install -y \
        fonts-jetbrains-mono \
        lxappearance \
        parcellite \
        dunst \
        preload \
        picom \
        feh \
        rofi \
        flameshot \
        xfce4-power-manager \
        nm-applet \
        gnome-themes-extra \
        policykit-1-gnome

What each package does:

  fonts-jetbrains-mono  — primary bar and terminal font
  lxappearance          — GTK theme switcher (run once to set dark theme)
  parcellite            — clipboard manager (X11 clipboard fix)
  dunst                 — notification daemon
  preload               — adaptive readahead daemon, speeds up app launches
  picom                 — compositor (transparency, shadows, no tearing)
  feh                   — wallpaper setter
  rofi                  — app launcher (bound to Super+Space)
  flameshot             — screenshot tool (bound to Print key)
  xfce4-power-manager   — lid close suspend, screen blank, battery tray icon
  nm-applet             — network manager systray icon
  gnome-themes-extra    — provides Adwaita/dark GTK themes for lxappearance
  policykit-1-gnome     — polkit agent (GUI password prompts)


Additional Builds (from source)
--------------------------------
The following suckless tools must be built and installed manually
before launching dwm:

  st (terminal):
    git clone https://git.suckless.org/st
    cd st && make && sudo make clean install

  dmenu (app launcher):
    git clone https://git.suckless.org/dmenu
    cd dmenu && make && sudo make clean install

  MegaSync (cloud storage, not in default Ubuntu repos):
    https://mega.io/desktop


Installation
------------
Clone the repository and build:

    git clone https://github.com/bakkeby/dwm-flexipatch.git dwm
    cd dwm
    make clean install

Patches are toggled in patches.def.h. After editing patches.def.h
or config.h, rebuild with:

    make clean && make && sudo make clean install


Running dwm
-----------
A LightDM session file is provided. Copy it to make dwm appear
as a session option on the login screen:

    sudo cp dwm.desktop /usr/share/xsessions/dwm.desktop

Then log out and select "dwm" from the session menu in LightDM.

To start dwm via startx instead, add to your ~/.xinitrc:

    exec dwm

To connect dwm to a specific display:

    DISPLAY=foo.bar:1 exec dwm


Autostart
---------
dwm will run ~/.dwm/autostart.sh on startup (via AUTOSTART_PATCH).
Create it if it does not exist:

    mkdir -p ~/.dwm
    touch ~/.dwm/autostart.sh
    chmod +x ~/.dwm/autostart.sh

paste this in the file 

    ``

    

A working example autostart.sh for this setup:

    #!/bin/sh
    /usr/lib/policykit-1-gnome/polkit-gnome-authentication-agent-1 &
    nm-applet &
    megasync &
    flameshot &
    parcellite &
    dunst &

    while true; do
        xsetroot -name "$(date '+%I:%M%p %A %d %B %Y')"
        sleep 1
    done &


Key Bindings (custom)
---------------------
MODKEY is set to Super (Mod4Mask).

  Super+Shift+Return        open terminal (st)
  Super+Space               rofi launcher
  Super+p                   dmenu launcher
  Print                     flameshot screenshot GUI
  Super+Shift+r             restart dwm (selfrestart)
  Super+Ctrl+Shift+q        restart dwm (restartsig)
  Super+Shift+q             quit dwm
  Super+Shift+c             close focused window

  Super+j / Super+k         focus next/prev window
  Super+Shift+j / k         move window in stack (movestack)
  Super+h / Super+l         resize master area
  Super+Shift+h / l         resize client cfact
  Super+Return              zoom window to master
  Super+Shift+Space         toggle floating
  Super+f                   floating layout
  Super+t                   tile layout
  Super+m                   monocle layout

  Super+1..9                view tag
  Super+Shift+1..9          move window to tag
  Super+Tab                 previous tag
  Super+Shift+Tab           shiftview left

  App launchers (Super+Ctrl+...):
    f = Firefox
    w = Chrome
    y = htop in kitty
    e = Nautilus
    c = Calculator
    o = Clocks
    n = Notion
    a = ChatGPT
    g = Grok
    Shift+t = Todoist
    Shift+m = Monkeytype
    Shift+s = Google Sheets
    Shift+n = Google Keep

  Gaps (Super+Ctrl+...):
    Super+Mod4+0             toggle gaps
    Super+Mod4+Shift+0       reset gaps
    Super+Mod4+u/i/o         increase all/inner/outer gaps
    Super+Mod4+Shift+u/i/o  decrease all/inner/outer gaps


Configuration
-------------
All configuration is done in config.h (auto-generated from config.def.h
on first build). Edit config.h directly for keybindings, colors, fonts,
rules, and gap sizes. Patch selection is done in patches.def.h.

After any change, rebuild:

    make clean && make && sudo make clean install

Then restart dwm with Super+Shift+r or Super+Ctrl+Shift+q.


